==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From [[strait]] and [[jacket]]
===Noun===
'''straitjacket'''
#A [[jacket]]-like garment with very long [[sleeve]]s which can be secured in place, thus preventing the wearer from moving his or her arms. Often used in [[psychiatric]] [[hospital]]s to prevent patients from injuring themselves or others.
===Alternate spellings===
*[[strait jacket]], [[strait-jacket]]
===Synonyms===
*[[strait waistcoat]] (dated)
===Translations===
*French: [[camisole de force]] {{f}}
*German: [[Zwangsjacke]] {{f}}
